\pard\pardeftab720\li360\fi-360\ri0\sa120\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 1.	Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat, then add 22g of butter and let it melt.\
2.	Cook half mushrooms (7 oz): Add half the mushrooms and cook for 2 mins. Add half the salt and pepper, then continue to cook for another 2 mins until most mushrooms are becoming golden. Then add half the garlic (6g) and cook until mushrooms are fully golden, and remove to a plate.\
3.	Cook remaining mushrooms: Melt remaining butter (22g), then cook remaining mushrooms per above (adding salt & pepper partway through, and garlic (6g) towards the end). Remove to a plate.\
